Leptobrachella sungi

is primarily found in northern Vietnam, specifically in the provinces of Vinh Phuc, Yen Bai, Lao Cai, Dien Bien, Phu Tho, Son La, and Tuyen Quang, as well as in Guangxi, China (

). Previous studies have indicated that 

L. sungi

was only observed in the SWDS area of Guangxi (

; 

). In our current study, we have identified a new range of 

L. sungi

in Guangxi, specifically in the Sishuihe Nature Reserve, located in Lingyun County, Guangxi, China (SSH, Fig. 
1
).
